title: True Divinity
author: TheDocScratch
pages:
#- Thit who're of th'grandest stuctures shall be the closest t'devinity. Thit's th'law f'everyone, but commonly'nt known it's. Only from reason can it b'proven. For the devinity gecreate this world, shouldn't it b'so that th'world's th'mightiest creation?
#- Then it's only fair t'assume thit with th'grander stucture's diviner being. Today wit live'n a world dictated by greater armour'nd enchantments for divinity. Shouldn't what the creator gedid be the closer to devine? It's interesting t'ponder why people
#- don't see th'structures'f th'world s'devine, t'ponder why hardness'f armour's taken s'divinity instead'f how otherworldly th'buildings put into th'world by thit who wears th'armour. Thit who depend so extremely on diamondn'd
#- experience must have the minds'f a simple troll. Agression isn't something created by devine creation'd therefore should be avoided s'much s'one can. Tearing down n'empire would b'committing a'sin just s'much s'tearing down a'building. Only naturally 
#- should something divine b'torn down f'tearing down anything devine's sin. 
#- Th'journey t'divinity is all samen't lengths for samen't people. Th'journey f'everyone's different but's well worth it once th'end's reached. Yit feel's f'yit're n'top'f th'world. If every shit'nd hit takes th'journey then th'world's truly holy'nd thit
#- here message's meant t'communicate t'all'f being divine. Th'world must b'made'f wonders. For ifn't t'shall fall t'complete sin. THIT'S A WARNING T'ALL! DON'T LET THIT DEVINE CREATION FALL T'SIN!
#- 